Dickey Fuller Test (ADF)

A sÃ©rie nÃ£o Ã© uma sÃ©rie estacionÃ¡ria e nem o log PorÃ©m a diferenÃ§a da P1 Ã© estacionÃ¡ria

Tratamento para time series

set.seed(123)
rm(df,p0, select)

algodao_timeseries <- p1 %>%select(c(Data,Valor_dÃ³lar))
algodao_timeseries$Data <- ymd(algodao_timeseries$Data)
algodao_timeseries <- algodao_timeseries %>% na.omit()

inds <- seq(as.Date("2019-02-01"), as.Date("2022-02-01"), by = "day")


algodao_timeseries2 <- ts(algodao_timeseries,     # Dados
           start = c(2019, as.numeric(format(inds[1], "%j"))),
           frequency = 365)
plot.ts(algodao_timeseries2)

## plot it

# Parametros NFCP
model_parameters_2F <- NFCP_parameters(N_factors = 2,
                                      GBM = TRUE,
                                      initial_states = FALSE,
                                      N_ME = 5)
## 
## ----------------------------------------------------------------
## 2 Factors model: first factor is a GBM
## 
## Risk Neutral SDE: 
## 
## log(s_t) = sum(x_t)
## 
## Where: 
## d x1_t    = mu_rn * dt  + sigma_1 * dW_1
## d x2_t    = - (lambda_2 + kappa_2 * x2_t) * dt  + sigma_2 * dW_2
## 
##  And: 
## 
## E(dW_1 * dW_2) = rho_1_2 * dt
print(model_parameters_2F)
##  [1] "mu"       "mu_rn"    "lambda_2" "kappa_2"  "sigma_1"  "sigma_2" 
##  [7] "rho_1_2"  "ME_1"     "ME_2"     "ME_3"     "ME_4"     "ME_5"
# Cada regiÃ£o possui um valor diferente da pluma de algodÃ£o
